      "writtenOn": "2019-03-02T01:03:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Only the Windows build of the syscall package has CreationFlags in its SysProcAttr. I\u0027m deliberately trying to keep the least amount of code possible in strategy_\u003cplatform\u003e.go files, because those are only compiled if you\u0027re on that platform (or if you remember to set GOOS env var).\n\nBy limiting the amount of code in strategy_windows.go, we ensure as much code as possible is always compiled, which helps prevent errors (e.g. if you make a change that breaks WindowsStrategy but the entire WindowsStrategy is defined in strategy_windows.go you might not realize until the Windows try bot runs because a simple \"go build\" without GOOS won\u0027t even compile it, but if you always compile WindowsStrategy you\u0027ll realize it locally).",
      "parentUuid": "1de1294f_39bb7fac",
